{
  "text": "Cultures were incubated in a humidified atmosphere at 37°C flushed with 5% CO 2 . At weekly intervals, half of the medium was replaced with fresh medium containing nonadherent cells recovered from the supernatant. After 5, 7 and 9 weeks, nonadherent cells and adherent cells were collected. Both types of cells were then assayed for colony-forming cells (CFC) in the presence of optimal concentrations of IL-3,GM-CSF, G-CSF, Epo and SCF, as described elsewhere. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] In this experiment, we also added 100 U/ml of IL-6, which had a maximal effect on the maturation of megakaryocyte progenitors in culture. [CITATION_5] ",
  "correct_citation": {
